	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Just to summarize, since people seem to be mixing <BR>
their words quite a bit, Spirit of Wolf is the <BR>
spell that shamen get at level 9 which will only <BR>
wear off over time or if you deliberately turn it <BR>
off.  It can be cast on anyone.  It is available<BR>
in Halas and presumably also in Grobb and Cabilis.<BR>
<BR>
Scale of Wolf is the level 24 shaman spell that is <BR>
faster than Spirit of Wolf but which now has been <BR>
fixed to only wear off if you turn it off or if <BR>
you cast or attack something.  Being attacked will <BR>
not turn it off.  You must be grouped with someone <BR>
to cast it on them.  The only place that I know <BR>
for certain this is available is from the shaman <BR>
spell merchant in Fironia who also has some of the <BR>
50+ spells.  I am guessing evil races can get it <BR>
somewhere, too, perhaps in the Overthere city.<BR>
<BR>
The spell in question for this page, though is <BR>
Spirit of Scale, which appears to simply cast <BR>
Scale of Wolf on the entire group.  Thus it is <BR>
also faster than Spirit of Wolf (quite a bit <BR>
faster at high levels) but will wear off if you <BR>
attack or cast anything.  It casts on the whole <BR>
group but only people in your group.  However, <BR>
Spirit of Scale is only dropped by 50+ creatures<BR>
in certain zones in Kunark and *cannot* be bought<BR>
from a merchant unless some fool sold it to that<BR>
merchant.  It is possible to trade in some spells<BR>
for others from one of the shamen npcs in Fironia<BR>
so presumably one can also get it that way, but<BR>
the spells you trade in likewise can only be found<BR>
on creatures and cannot be bought from npc's. <BR>
None of these are no drop, as far as I know, so <BR>
it is also possible to buy them from other players<BR>
who find them.<BR>
<BR>
I would not worry overmuch about researching these<BR>
very high level spells online, though, because by<BR>
the time you are high enough to use them you will<BR>
know all there is to know about them from other<BR>
people, anyway.<BR>
<BR>
Good hunting to ye!
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
